        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down</placeName>
                    <date>March 2nd</date>
                    <salute>My dear Galton,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have signed the enclosed with much pleasure.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>You shall hear about germination of the Peas in a few days.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>Yours sincerely, | C. Darwin.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10395.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Francis Galton, 16 February 1876</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The enclosure has not been identified.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD was assisting Galton with experiments on sweetpeas (<hi rend="italic">Lathyrus odoratus</hi>); see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10395.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Francis Galton, 16 February 1876</ref> and n. 1.</note>
        </div>        
            
